President Muhammadu Buhari has urged veteran journalist, Chief Abiodun Adeniyi, to continue to avail the country and the younger generation the wealth of his experience. In a message on Tuesday in Abuja by his Special Adviser (SA) on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina, the President hailed Chief Adeniyi on his 80th anniversary. He lauded his commitment to the journalism profession, where he mentored many generations of younger professionals. “President Muhammadu Buhari salutes veteran journalist and one of the founding fathers of state radio stations in the country, Chief Abiodun Adeniyi, as he turns 80 on December 25. “Adeniyi, with about six decades of journalism experience tucked under his belt, was one of the pioneer staff of Radio Lagos, where he rose to commanding heights, before retiring into advertising practice, where he equally made a grand showing…”